complaints.title: Damaged Roads and Waterlogging near Kanke Road, Pandra Chowk
complaints.details:
Residents and daily commuters around Kanke Road, particularly near Pandra Chowk and the approach to CMPDI Gate, are struggling with poor road and drainage conditions.

Key issues observed:

Damaged Road Surface: Multiple deep potholes along the stretch cause traffic congestion and frequent two-wheeler accidents.

Waterlogging: During rainfall, clogged roadside drains lead to waterlogging, with knee-deep water making the area inaccessible.

Public Safety Concerns: Stagnant water near Pandra Chowk has become a breeding ground for mosquitoes, raising fears of dengue and malaria.

Traffic Disruptions: Autos and buses are forced to divert, worsening traffic jams in peak hours.

complaints.title: Irregular Drinking Water Supply at Doranda, Ward 32 (near St. Annes School)
complaints.details:
Residents of Doranda, Ward 32, especially those living in the locality around St. Annes School and Doranda Bazar Road, are facing irregular water supply for the past two weeks.

Key observations:

Water supply is limited to once every two days, and even then, the pressure is very low.

Families are forced to rely on private water tankers, adding to their expenses.

Schools and small shops in the area are struggling with sanitation due to lack of clean water.

Elderly residents and low-income families are the most affected, as they cannot afford alternate water sources.

Local complaints have been made to the water supply office, but no improvement has been noted.

complaints.title: Broken Public Toilets at Albert Ekka Chowk
complaints.details:
The public toilet complex near Albert Ekka Chowk, one of Ranchis busiest intersections, has been in a severely neglected condition for more than a month.

Key observations:

Out of 10 toilet units, only 3 are functional; others have broken doors, leaking taps, and no running water.

Hygiene standards are poor  overflowing septic tanks and foul odor deter people from using the facility.

Women and elderly citizens are especially affected, as there are no safe and clean alternatives nearby.

Vendors and daily commuters report open urination around the chowk due to lack of usable facilities, creating both sanitation and image problems for the city center.

Despite being located in a high-visibility area, no maintenance team has been deployed recently.

complaints.title: Neglected Childrens Park at Morabadi Ground
complaints.details:
The childrens park located near Morabadi Ground, opposite Birsa Munda Football Stadium, has been poorly maintained for several months, making it unsafe and unusable for families.

Key observations:

Several play equipment (swings, slides, see-saws) are broken or rusted, posing a danger to children.

The parks fencing is damaged, allowing stray animals to enter freely.

Grass and weeds are overgrown, reducing open play space.

Lighting inside the park is inadequate, leaving dark spots after sunset.

Despite repeated requests from local residents associations, no maintenance work has been carried out.

complaints.title: Open Drain Causing Health Hazards at Lalpur Road, Near GEL Church Complex
complaints.details:
An open drain along Lalpur Road, near the GEL Church Complex and adjacent residential lanes, has been left uncovered and poorly maintained for several months.

Key observations:

The drain is filled with stagnant water, plastic, and food waste, creating a strong foul odor.

During rains, the drain overflows onto the road, causing waterlogging and making the stretch slippery and unsafe.

Residents nearby have reported an increase in mosquitoes and flies, raising concerns of dengue and malaria outbreaks.

Pedestrians, especially school children using the road, are at risk of slipping or falling into the open drain.

Despite complaints to the local ward office, no covering or cleaning has been done in the last two months.

complaints.title: Broken Footpath Slabs at Main Road, Near Firayalal Chowk
complaints.details:
The footpath along Main Road near Firayalal Chowk, a high-footfall commercial area, has several broken and missing concrete slabs. This poses a serious risk to pedestrians, especially elderly citizens and children.

Key observations:

At least six slabs are broken or missing, leaving large open gaps.

During evening hours, poor lighting makes these gaps hard to notice, increasing chances of accidents.

A few residents have already reported minor injuries from tripping or stepping into the openings.

Shopkeepers nearby often place temporary boards over the gaps, but these are unstable and unsafe.

Despite being a central location, the damage has remained unattended for more than one month.

contextAssessment.reasoning: All four municipal context questions regarding the nature/type of issue, location, scope, and urgency level are clearly and sufficiently addressed in the provided report details. The report is actionable with the current information.

departmentAllocation.summary: Broken footpath slabs near Modonlal Gamcha Dokan on Main Road, near Firayalal Chowk, pose a serious safety risk to pedestrians, especially during evening hours due to poor lighting. At least one slab is damaged, leading to reported minor injuries.

complaints.title: Damaged Bus Stop Shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk
complaints.details:
The bus stop shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk, one of Ranchis busiest bus junctions, has been damaged and remains in disrepair for over a month.

Key observations:

The roof sheets are broken and partially missing, offering no protection during rain or sun.

The seating benches are rusted and some are broken, making it unsafe for commuters.

Commuters, including school children and office workers, are forced to stand on the roadside.

During rains, people spill onto the main road, creating traffic obstructions and safety hazards.

Despite being an important stop for multiple city routes, no maintenance work has been carried out.

contextAssessment.reasoning: The report provides sufficient detail to answer all municipal context questions. departmentAllocation.summary: Damaged bus stop shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk with broken roof and unsafe benches, posing safety hazards and causing inconvenience for commuters and traffic.

complaints.title: Waterlogging at Entrance of Government Girls High School, Bariatu
complaints.details:
The entrance road of Government Girls High School, Bariatu, gets heavily waterlogged after even moderate rainfall due to poor drainage. This has been a recurring problem for the last two months.

Key observations:

Students and teachers are forced to wade through knee-deep water to enter the school.

The stagnant water often remains for 23 days after rainfall, creating breeding grounds for mosquitoes.

Parents have raised concerns about children slipping and injuring themselves.

The school authorities have complained multiple times to the local ward office but no drain-cleaning or repair work has been carried out.

This situation is disrupting attendance and creating an unsafe learning environment.

allocatedDepartment.analysis: Broken footpath slabs near Modonlal Gamcha Dokan on Main Road, near Firayalal Chowk, pose a serious safety risk to pedestrians, especially during evening hours due to poor lighting. At least one slab is damaged, leading to reported minor injuries.

allocatedDepartment.title: Damaged Bus Stop Shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk
allocatedDepartment.details:
The bus stop shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk, one of Ranchis busiest bus junctions, has been damaged and remains in disrepair for over a month.

Key observations:

The roof sheets are broken and partially missing, offering no protection during rain or sun.

The seating benches are rusted and some are broken, making it unsafe for commuters.

Commuters, including school children and office workers, are forced to stand on the roadside.

During rains, people spill onto the main road, creating traffic obstructions and safety hazards.

Despite being an important stop for multiple city routes, no maintenance work has been carried out.
allocatedDepartment.analysis: Damaged bus stop shelter at Kanta Toli Chowk with broken roof and unsafe benches, posing safety hazards and causing inconvenience for commuters and traffic.

allocatedDepartment.title: Waterlogging at Entrance of Government Girls High School, Bariatu
allocatedDepartment.details:
The entrance road of Government Girls High School, Bariatu, gets heavily waterlogged after even moderate rainfall due to poor drainage. This has been a recurring problem for the last two months.

Key observations:

Students and teachers are forced to wade through knee-deep water to enter the school.

The stagnant water often remains for 23 days after rainfall, creating breeding grounds for mosquitoes.

Parents have raised concerns about children slipping and injuring themselves.

The school authorities have complained multiple times to the local ward office but no drain-cleaning or repair work has been carried out.

This situation is disrupting attendance and creating an unsafe learning environment.
allocatedDepartment.analysis: Waterlogging at the entrance of Government Girls High School, Bariatu, due to poor drainage. Stagnant water creates health hazards (mosquitoes) and safety risks (slipping), disrupting school attendance. Urgent drain-cleaning and repair are required.
